PRIMARY: UI Redesign:
    - Rebuild the frontend with Claude using the design skill with specs

---

Authentication:
    - Microsoft OAuth2 device code flow (show code + link, poll for completion)
    - Xbox Live token exchange (MSA -> XBL -> XSTS -> Minecraft)
    - Store tokens in OS keychain (keyring crate)
    - Token refresh on app startup
    - Login page UI (friendly "Sign in with Microsoft" flow)
    - Profile display in sidebar (username + avatar)
    - Logout functionality

Vanilla Minecraft Launch:
    - Fetch version manifest from piston-meta.mojang.com
    - Download version JSON, client JAR, libraries, assets
    - OS-conditional library filtering (macOS/Windows rules)
    - Build classpath and JVM argument strings
    - Java auto-detection (JAVA_HOME, common paths, parse version)
    - Adoptium JRE auto-download if no suitable Java found
    - Spawn Minecraft process and capture stdout/stderr
    - Stream game logs to frontend

Modpack Installation:
    - Download .mrpack from Modrinth version files
    - Parse modrinth.index.json from ZIP
    - Read dependencies (MC version, loader type + version)
    - Parallel file downloads with hash verification (SHA-512)
    - Extract overrides/ and client-overrides/ into .minecraft
    - Install Fabric loader (download profile JSON + libraries)
    - Install Forge/NeoForge/Quilt loaders
    - Write file_manifest.json (hashes of all installed files)
    - Write last_mrpack_index.json (for future update diffs)
    - Installation progress UI with per-file tracking

Modpack Browser:
    - Install button on modpack cards (version selector)
    - Modpack detail view (description, versions, install)
    - Pagination / infinite scroll for search results
    - Loading states and error handling

Update System:
    - Check for updates on app launch (compare version IDs)
    - "Update available" badge on instance cards
    - Diff engine (compare old vs new modrinth.index.json)
    - Compute add/update/remove/skip actions
    - Update confirmation UI (show what will change)
    - Apply updates (download new, delete removed, skip locked)
    - Detect user-modified files (hash current vs manifest)
    - Conflict resolution dialog (keep yours / update / view diff)

File Lock System:
    - File tree component (expandable directory view)
    - Search bar to filter files by path/name
    - Lock toggle (padlock icon on each file)
    - Directory-level locks (lock everything inside a folder)
    - Quick-lock suggestions (options.txt, servers.dat, config/)
    - Explanation banner for non-technical users
    - Integration with update diff engine (skip locked files)

Instance Management:
    - Instance detail page (overview, mods list, files, settings)
    - Instance-specific settings (Java path, memory, JVM args, resolution)
    - Instance deletion with confirmation dialog
    - Instance renaming
    - Last played timestamp tracking

UI Polish:
    - Page transitions (fly/fade between pages)
    - List animations (items entering/leaving)
    - Download progress in status bar (mini progress bar)
    - Toast notifications (success/error/info)
    - Tooltips on buttons and icons
    - Loading skeletons instead of "Loading..." text
    - Error states with retry buttons

Settings Page:
    - Default memory selector (wired to actual setting)
    - Download directory picker
    - Concurrent download limit
    - Check for updates on launch toggle
    - Close launcher on game start toggle
    - Clear cache button

---

Distribution:
    - macOS code signing and notarization
    - Windows code signing
    - GitHub Actions CI (build both platforms)
    - Tauri auto-updater for Lantern itself
    - GitHub Releases workflow
